# Plan — Maryland Driveway Restore
## Status: READY (research integrated)

---

## Demo Concept

**Type:** Full-featured static HTML/CSS/JS site (9 pages + assets), hosted at
`michaelwegter.com/demos/maryland-driveway-restore/`. Flask blueprint receives
and persists estimate form submissions. This is the PRIMARY build target — static
demo reproduces the Phase 1 look, feel, and visitor experience exactly. The
proposal describes how the same build pattern maps to WordPress + Bricks Builder
for the actual delivery.

**Core narrative:** "Restore, Don't Replace" — a premium lead-generation site for
a Maryland driveway restoration company. The demo IS the proof: 9 fully navigable,
mobile-first pages with working lead capture, before/after drag slider, filterable
gallery lightbox, service-area map, embedded schema, and GA4 event hooks.

**WP Docker stretch (CEO-gated only):** If CEO approves after reviewing the
static demo quality, the builder MAY attempt a real WP container via Flask bridge
blueprint at `/demos/maryland-driveway-restore-wp/`. Flask bridge only — no
separate tunnel ingress. Risk: Docker not confirmed installed on Surface, URL
rewriting behind a sub-path bridge is complex. Critical path does NOT depend on
this.

---

## Design System (locked — do NOT use michaelwegter.com palette)

```
Palette:
  charcoal-deep:   #1A1D1A   (nav, footer, primary dark backgrounds)
  charcoal-mid:    #2C302C   (alternate sections, card backgrounds)
  white:           #FFFFFF   (text on dark, pure backgrounds)
  off-white:       #F5F4F0   (light section backgrounds)
  forest-green:    #2F5D3A   (primary CTA color, accent, highlights)
  green-light:     #4A8C5C   (hover states, secondary accents)
  gold-muted:      #C9A84C   (star ratings, premium badges, subtle accents)

Typography:
  Headings:   Playfair Display (Google Fonts) — luxury serif, editorial weight
  Body:       Inter (Google Fonts) — clean, legible sans
  Labels/CTA: Inter 600-700, slight letter-spacing, uppercase for badge labels

Layout:
  Max content width: 1200px centered
  Section vertical padding: 80px desktop / 40px mobile
  Whitespace-first, photography-led — full-bleed hero, oversized before/after
  No cramming; each section breathes

Mobile (design-first breakpoints):
  Primary: 480px (phone)
  Secondary: 768px (tablet)
  Sticky CTA bar: position:fixed bottom:0 (Call Now + Text a Photo), always visible
  Touch targets: min 48x48px
  Hamburger nav on mobile, full horizontal nav on desktop
  Images: loading="lazy", width/height set to prevent layout shift
```

---

## Page Architecture (9 pages)

| File | Route | Key Features |
|------|-------|-------------|
| `index.html` | / (homepage) | Hero before/after drag slider, benefits strip, process steps (4 steps), pricing preview cards, gallery 6-thumbnail preview, testimonials/reviews, FAQ accordion, estimate form, footer |
| `driveway-restoration.html` | /driveway-restoration | Process breakdown, materials, timeline, before/after comparison, "restore vs replace" cost comparison, Service schema JSON-LD |
| `pricing.html` | /pricing | 3-tier pricing table (Essential/Premium/Complete), add-ons list, vs-replacement cost comparison, FAQ strip, CTA |
| `gallery.html` | /gallery | 16-24 before/after image grid, JS lightbox (vanilla), filter buttons by project type |
| `about.html` | /about | Company mission, restore-not-replace ethos, environmental/tree-planting commitment, credentials/experience, team headshots placeholder |
| `faq.html` | /faq | Full FAQ accordion (20+ questions), FAQPage schema JSON-LD, sidebar CTA |
| `contact.html` | /contact | Full lead-capture form (name, email, phone, address, project description, photo upload, service area select), embedded Google Map iframe, response-time promise |
| `service-areas.html` | /service-areas | MD county/city grid list + embedded map, Annapolis base, coverage zones, local keyword anchor text |
| `free-estimate.html` | /free-estimate | QR target page: single powerful before/after, 3-bullet value prop, Call Now CTA, Text a Photo CTA, minimal 5-field form |

---

## Feature Implementation Map

| Brief Requirement | Demo Implementation |
|------------------|-------------------|
| Before/after hero slider | `img-comparison-slider` web component (CDN import) — drag handle, keyboard accessible |
| Before/after images | Single Pexels/Unsplash residential driveway photo; CSS `filter: grayscale(80%) brightness(1.4)` for "before", `filter: brightness(0.85) saturate(1.2)` for "after" |
| Sticky Call Now + Text a Photo | `position:fixed; bottom:0; z-index:1000` bar with two colored buttons, mobile-only via CSS |
| Estimate form + photo upload | `<form>` with `<input type="file" accept="image/*">`, posts to Flask `POST /demos/maryland-driveway-restore/submit` |
| Service area map | Embedded Google Maps iframe (Annapolis, MD center) with satellite view; fallback SVG Maryland county map |
| LocalBusiness schema | JSON-LD in `<head>` of every page: `HomeAndConstructionBusiness` subtype, address, phone, service area |
| FAQPage schema | JSON-LD on `faq.html` and in the homepage FAQ section |
| Service schema | JSON-LD on `driveway-restoration.html` |
| AggregateRating schema | JSON-LD on homepage (4.9 stars, 47 reviews placeholder) |
| BreadcrumbList schema | JSON-LD on all inner pages |
| GA4 event hooks | `gtag('event', ...)` calls: `form_submit`, `cta_click_call`, `cta_click_text`, `gallery_view`, `pricing_view` |
| XML sitemap | `sitemap.xml` in demo root, all 9 pages with priority weights |
| Unique title + meta per page | Each file: `<title>` with geo + keyword + brand, `<meta name="description">` 150-160 chars |
| H1-H3 hierarchy | Single H1 per page aligned to target keyword, logical sub-headings |
| Image ALT text | All `<img>` tags: descriptive keyword-inclusive alt attributes |
| Internal linking | Nav, footer, in-page CTAs cross-link between all pages |
| Gallery lightbox | Vanilla JS lightbox — click thumbnail, overlay opens with before/after pair, keyboard navigation |
| Core Web Vitals | `loading="lazy"` on all below-fold images, minified inline CSS critical path, no render-blocking scripts |
| /free-estimate QR page | Distinct `free-estimate.html`, linked from footer and contact page; not the homepage |

