## fortherecordmn.com Proof Framing (locked from research)

**Do NOT claim specific rankings or traffic numbers** (private dashboard data).

Cover letter framing:
> "For a Minnesota wedding DJ, I configured a 6-page local service site with an XML sitemap (all pages indexed with priority weights), geo-targeted title structure ('Brand | Location | Primary Service'), logical /slug URL hierarchy, and GA4/GSC integration — the same on-page foundation this project requires. Metrics are client-confidential; happy to share a screen share on a call."

---

## Competitive Differentiation (from research)

**Market gap identified:** Zero Maryland driveway competitors use a premium aesthetic. Asphalt Star (asphaltstar.com) is the strongest (7.5/10, 1957 heritage, local schema) but uses a generic contractor template. Every other player is 3-5/10. No competitor has:
- Before/after hero slider
- "Restore, don't replace" anti-replacement framing
- Apple/RH aesthetic (whitespace, charcoal, forest green, serif headings)
- Environmental/sustainability angle
- Cinematic photography

**Proposal positioning line:** "Every other driveway company in Maryland sells you a new driveway. Maryland Driveway Restore sells you the one you have, made better."

This differentiation should appear in: cover letter intro, homepage hero subhead, About page mission statement, one-pager headline.

---

## Flask Blueprint

`maryland_driveway_blueprint.py` in `mw-backend/`:
- `POST /demos/maryland-driveway-restore/submit` — name, email, phone, address, description, optional file; stores in SQLite `mw.db` table `mdr_leads`; returns `{"ok": true}`
- `GET /demos/maryland-driveway-restore/leads` — JWT-protected, returns all leads as JSON for Michael to review
- CORS: open for `https://michaelwegter.com`

